Package wtf.file.api.color

Enum-Klasse ColorSpace

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<ColorSpace>
wtf.file.api.color.ColorSpace
Alle implementierten Schnittstellen:
Serializable, Comparable<ColorSpace>, Constable
public enum ColorSpace extends Enum<ColorSpace>
Represents predefined color spaces, each defined by a specific set of ColorChannels.

This enum supports common color models such as Grayscale, RGB, CMY, HSV, and YCbCr, with optional alpha channels (both fixed and dynamic).

Each color space can provide its list of channels and a default color map, which currently defaults all channel values to zero (e.g., black or fully transparent).

    • defaultColor

      public Map<ColorChannel,DefaultValue> defaultColor()
      Returns a default color value map for this color space.

      By default, all channels are assigned a value of 0 via ZeroDefaultValue. This represents black or fully transparent values, depending on the channel.

      Gibt zurück:
      a map from each ColorChannel to its DefaultValue
